  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scale up of reception and CCCM services in Monguno and Ngala LGA by providing quality Site facilitation and management while contributing at camp de-congestion</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Though the proposed intervention INTERSOS aims to provide emergency humanitarian assistance at Reception Centers and Camp settings in Ngala and Monguno LGAs. The rationale of the project is to address critical humanitarian needs which were not covered by the previous interventions as well as provide emergency humanitarian assistance for the newly displaced in the targeted locations. In the project focus areas, INTERSOS will scale up its intervention with provision of basic reception and hosting services to the new arrivals. INTERSOS will strive to fulfill the basic humanitarian needs of the most vulnerable communities through the provision of adequate temporary housing solutions and reception center facilities. With the assistance of other services providers, the project will enhance the different referral pathways and the referral mechanism. 
The project has been designed to meet the affected population&#x2019;s most urgent needs in a sustainable way that empowers local communities and service providers by working through existing structures such as camp committees.</narrative>
  </description>
